In mathematics, the '''Berry–Robbins problem''' asks whether there is a continuous map from [[configuration (geometry)|configurations]] of ''n'' points in '''R'''<sup>3</sup> to the [[flag manifold]] ''U''(''n'')/''T''<sup>''n''</sup> that is compatible with the [[Group action (mathematics)|action]] of the [[symmetric group]] on ''n'' points. It was posed by {{harvs|txt|last1=Berry|last2=Robbins|year=1997|author1-link=Michael Berry (physicist)}} and solved positively by {{harvs|txt|last=Atiyah|authorlink=Michael Atiyah|year=2000}}.

==See also==
*[[Atiyah conjecture on configurations]]

==References==
