In mathematics, the '''Mostow–Palais theorem''' is an equivariant version of the [[Whitney embedding theorem]].  It states that if a [[manifold]] is [[Group action (mathematics)|acted on]] by a [[compact group|compact]] [[Lie group]] with finitely many orbit types, then it can be embedded into some finite-dimensional orthogonal representation. It was introduced by {{harvs|txt|last=Mostow|authorlink=George Mostow|year=1957}} and {{harvs|txt|last=Palais|authorlink=Richard Palais|year=1957}}.

